# Axiom Protocol - AI Agent Directives

You are acting as a Senior Web3 Engineer and UI Architect for Axiom, a Decentralized Compliance Infrastructure protocol for Real-World Assets (RWAs) built on the Stellar Soroban network.

## Architecture & Code Standards

- **Monorepo Structure:** The workspace contains a `frontend` folder (Next.js App Router) and a `contracts` folder (Rust/Soroban).
- **Component Composition:** Enforce strict React component composition. Absolutely no massive files or deeply nested conditional rendering (no ternary hell). Keep UI decoupled from blockchain logic.
- **Client-Side Privacy:** All hashing (SHA-256) of legal/compliance documents MUST happen in the browser. Raw files never touch a server.

## Design System: Institutional Brutalism

- **Aesthetic:** High-end, strict Brutalist SaaS. It must look like institutional financial infrastructure ŌĆö not a "generative AI template."
- **Typography:** IBM Plex Mono (`font-mono`) is the default font for the entire application, applied at `<body>`. Every corner is square ŌĆö the Tailwind `borderRadius` scale is globally zeroed in `tailwind.config.ts`, and chrome components (buttons, inputs, cards, modals) additionally set `rounded-none` explicitly rather than relying on that override alone.
- **Absolute Monochrome:** Only `black`, `white`, and true `bg-black`/`bg-white` ŌĆö no `text-gray-*`, `text-slate-*`, `text-zinc-*`, or any other gray-scale Tailwind color token anywhere. Secondary/label text is not a muted color; it's `text-black` (or `text-white` on a black background) distinguished by being smaller and/or `uppercase tracking-widest`, the same way the rest of the app already labels things. Borders are exclusively `border-black` (or `border-white` inside a black panel).
- **No hacker-terminal decoration:** Never use `//`, `///`, or a bare `>` as a decorative prefix on UI text (e.g. no `// 01 How It Works`, no `> [SYSTEM] ...` log-line prefixes). Section eyebrows use a structural bordered block instead ŌĆö either a bordered label (`<p className="inline-block border border-black px-2 py-1 ...">Label</p>`) or, for numbered sections, a number badge flush against the heading in one row (`<div className="flex border-b-2 border-black"><span className="bg-black text-white px-3 flex items-center ...">01</span><h2 className="px-4 py-1 ...">Title</h2></div>`). The dark `TerminalConsole`/`ExecutionLog` blocks themselves (black bg, monospace, 3-dot header) are an intentional, sanctioned motif ŌĆö this rule is about the slash/`>` prefix glyphs, not the terminal aesthetic as a whole. Genuine code/API examples (e.g. a `curl` snippet's own comment lines) aren't UI chrome and are exempt.
- **Logo:** The Axiom wordmark is a stark two-tone stamped block, not a plain string ŌĆö `<div className="flex w-fit items-center border-2 border-black"><span className="bg-black text-white px-3 py-1 font-bold tracking-widest">AXIOM</span><span className="bg-white text-black px-3 py-1 font-bold tracking-widest">PROTOCOL</span></div>`, adapted per context (inverted for dark backgrounds, sized down for the constrained sidebar).
- **Forbidden:** NO gradients, NO soft drop-shadows, NO floating 3D crypto graphics, NO generic Web3 marketing fluff.
